01/03/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- The country's two main factions -- the ruling Socialist Party and the opposition Democratic Party -- finally reached agreement Monday (28 February) on a new map of electoral zones, resolving a lengthy deadlock that threatened to delay this summer's parliamentary elections.
Both the OSCE Presence in Albania and the Council of Europe's Tirana office praised the agreement and urged parliament to approve it as soon as possible.
In other news, Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano visits Athens later this week.
On Monday, Greek Ambassador to Albania Pantelis Carcabassis said that Albania would remain the focus of Greek efforts to back EU integration processes in the region via investments.
(Albanian News - 01/03/05;
OSCE Web site - 28/02/05)
